    "raw_text": "Summary: The analysis shows a weak positive correlation between Registration Lead Time and Average Score. This suggests that students who register earlier tend to have slightly higher average scores, but the relationship is not strong enough to draw definitive conclusions.\n\nInsights: Weak Positive Correlation: The correlation coefficient of 0.0017 indicates a weak positive relationship between the number of days before course start and the average score. This means that as registration lead time increases, average scores tend to increase slightly, but the effect is minimal.\n\nEducational implications: Early registration may provide some benefits, but it is not the sole factor influencing student performance.\n\nRecommendations: medium - Encourage students to register early for courses. - While the correlation is weak, early registration could still help students feel more prepared and organized.",
